modules.description: Provides encoding of audio data into AAC format using specific bitstream operations and sample rate conversion. Works with raw audio buffers and configuration parameters for bit rate and channel layout. Used to generate compressed audio streams for streaming applications and embedded systems.

Provides functions to encode strings using specific encoding parameters, including methods to generate output strings and track encoded byte counts. Works with custom parameters and encoding state objects, supporting both string and buffer inputs. Enables precise control over encoding processes, such as handling exceptions and determining minimum input sizes.
